HEADWORD: Thiller
<hw>Thill"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The horse which goes
between the thills, or shafts, and supports them; also, the last horse
in a team; -- called also <altname>thill horse</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

